examples.en: The train from New York is now arriving.
We're arriving on Christmas Eve.
She chided us for arriving late.
Arriving late is a woman's prerogative.
He was angry because of their arriving late.
We daren't bet on the train arriving on time.
People were arriving by the carload.
The package should be arriving late next week.
The package should be arriving early next week.
Workers are penalized for arriving late for work.
They had to consult before arriving at a decision.
Arriving late won't create a very favourable impression.
He cursed his bad luck in arriving just after she'd left.
He had his car stolen within minutes of arriving at the office.
They'll be arriving soon. We don't have much more time to prepare.
The sailors were glad to be arriving in port after their long voyage.
A brassy customer insisted on arriving late and still being taken first.
We'll be arriving around noon. That's assuming that our flight is on time.
I wouldn't bargain on the speaker arriving soon, as he's got a long way to come.
Connie's going to land herself in big trouble if she keeps arriving late for work.
Apart from the bus arriving late, everything else seemed to be going according to plan.
The policeman proved to be our savior, arriving on the scene just as we were about to be mugged.
As far as I know, they're arriving on Saturday (=used when you think something is true but are not sure).
The father was forced to rebuke his son for the spendthrift ways he had adopted since arriving at college.
The arriving national guardsmen were forced to live in a hutment until permanent barracks could be constructed.
International Airport is something of a misnomer, since almost all the arriving and departing flights are local.
